Fragmented Home Healthcare is an extremely fragmented industry with roughly ,000 licenses in the The Top agencies all have less than a 6% individual market share and the agencies outside of the Top have less than a 1% individual market That leaves about % of the market being dominated by small home health providers that employ fewer than workers in their Motivated Sellers Did you know an estimated ,000 baby boomers are retiring each day? With baby boomer business owners now reaching retirement age, there‚Äôs a plethora of highly motivated Our acquisition strategy is to vet and acquire the agencies with great track records and sound growth Leverage We can use the SBA or commercial debt to intelligently leverage transactions and increase ROI (the cost of debt today is much cheaper than equity). Our access to debt financing is growing as we continue to prove ourselves as Banks are overflowing with cash and are looking for good operators to entrust with Growth The total Market Cap is $281.8B and is forecasted to grow to $515.6B by There is Total Home Health claims per There is expected to be a % CAGR (Compound Annual Growth Rate) and the population of + will grow from % to % of the entire population by LEADERSHIP Jeff Knighton, CPA M&A Accounting Barbara Sico Home Healthcare Operations Douglas Densmore M&A Legal Josie Ross Home Healthcare HR Charley Majors M&A Advisory Chairman Amy Breslin Home Healthcare M&A Jayson Norris President Tim Bradbury Director OUR CLIENT‚ÄôS CONTACT US Lynchburg, VA Name First Name Last Name Email Subject Message Thank you! Sustainable Commerce - Manifest Skip to content WHAT S MORE IMPORTANT? SUSTAINABILITY OR CX? Overview Solutions Use Cases Partners Market Analysis Resources Menu Overview Solutions Use Cases Partners Market Analysis Resources Let s Talk Metrics That Count Which is more important: Sustainability or CX? Presented by Manifest by George Wojciechowski, Peter Hillowe Contributing data from Definite Articles, PiperWai, SUAVS, Thousand Fell, TopFoxx, Wipeco, and EcoCart Table of Contents Introduction and hypothesis:: Brands are looking for improved sustainability tools and logistics tools separately from one Sustainability is customer experience (CX). Qualification for sustainable commerce development Sustainability metrics important to the transnational nature of commerce Consumer sustainability metric Data Deep Dive (Sustainability):: What we found out about 5 leading sustainable brands that are focused on sustainability in their product packaging and shipping Data Deep Dive (CX):: What we found out about those same 5 brands and their traditional logistics KPIs Do you really have to prioritize one over the other or are brands just looking in the wrong places? World Food Forum: The World Food Forum powered by global youth EN ES Tracks Youth Action Innovation Lab Education Cooking Film Music Highlights Year in review Events Social wall Champions Join us Your browser does not support the video WFF Year in Review The World Food Forum About us Guiding principles The World Food Forum While we currently produce enough food to feed every man, woman, and child in the world, there are up to million people who are hungry , a number which is growing in the wake of the An increase in threats like pests, plagues, conflict, and climate change are compounding this global food crisis . To mobilize action and identify solutions to address these threats, we launched the World Food Forum (WFF) ‚Äì a movement and network to transform our food systems to achieve the Sustainable Development Goals ( SDGs ), in particular ‚Äú zero hunger ‚Äù. With events, dialogue and outreach extending throughout the year , the WFF flagship event took place in October It gathered youth to drive awareness, foster engagement, and mobilized action in support of systems transformation . This recurring forum features a range of events, including Youth Action Assemby , Innovation Labs , Educational Activities , Cooking , Film and Music . Together we can build back better and create a better food future for Be part of the Join About us The World Food Forum ( WFF ) is an independent global network of partners, created for and led by youth, to spark a movement to transform our systems and achieve the Sustainable Development Goals ( SDGs ), including ‚ÄúZero Hunger‚Äù. Aligning with the core principles of the United Nations (UN) Food Systems Summit , the WFF aims to serve as the premier platform to engage and harness the passion of youth, galvanizing action and identifying solutions to the growing challenges facing our The WFF was conceived by the Youth Committee of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations ( FAO ) - a specialized agency of the UN, leading international efforts to sustainably defeat hunger and Formed and led by youthful staff, FAO‚Äôs Youth Committee was established in to tap into the potential of young employees as catalysts for change and to spark a global youth Many youth partners from across the UN, as well as public and private institutions have since associated themselves with the WFF, and now embody a truly forum that works as a network for the transformation of our food Guiding principles Sustainably feeding close to billion people by is an unprecedented challenge that requires global awareness and bold action . A profound and systemic transformation of systems is needed in order to nourish the nearly million people who are hungry today ‚Äì and the additional 2 billion people the world will have by In alignment with the core principles of the United Nations (UN) Food Systems Summit , the Agenda for Sutainable Development , and the strategic framework of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN , the World Food Forum (WFF) engages and empowers youth to find innovative and actionable solutions that can create more efficient, inclusive, resilient and sustainable systems for all . About Acupuncture - Be Well Holistic Care - Orlando Acupuncture, Massage, Skincare & Sugaring Skip to content Be Well Holistic Care - Orlando Acupuncture, Massage, Skincare & Sugaring Menu Close Book Now About Open menu Meet your Be Well Team FAQ Services Open menu Acupuncture Massage Skincare Sugaring Salt Therapy Wellness Journal Memberships Gift Cards Contact About Acupuncture What is Acupuncture? Acupuncture is used to promote the body‚Äôs remarkable An acupuncture treatment involves the insertion and manipulation of flexible, needles at specific points on the body, utilizing the nervous system network along the fascial plane, where your energy Acupuncture allows the body to return to its natural state of balance and harmony . Many patients find the sensations produced by acupuncture treatment to be a deeply relaxing, meditative experience both mentally and physically, and it is not uncommon for patients to fall asleep during this Origins of Acupuncture Acupuncture has been studied, further developed and ceaselessly researched while being used to effectively treat and prevent conditions for thousands of The initial discovery of acupuncture took place in East Asia, where illnesses are treated in a holistic manner that considers the impact of mental and emotional Based on this holistic approach, we examine illness from the perspective that stress causes disharmony and eventually imbalance, which disrupts a person‚Äôs ability to effectively deal with Over time, this weakens their ability to prevent and heal from illness, as we are all designed to naturally Acupuncture is only one method of treatment that exists within a wide scope of practices beneath the ancient system of East Asian Why Acupuncture? When it comes to our health, even though many of us are aware of our basic biology, most of us don‚Äôt think much about the parts of ourselves we don‚Äôt see‚Äîour emotions, energy levels, thoughts and even our cells are, for the most part, invisible to us during our lives, yet we would never deny their Our energy, similar to the blood in our vessels, travels along a specific pathway called a channel, or This energy, though it moves along this channel without us perceiving it most of the time, can be experienced during an acupuncture How Acupuncture is Administered Using very fine, and surgical, stainless steel needles on specific points along the body, we are able to restore that balance and correct the The needles, once inserted, act as conductors for this , the connection required to keep harmony and balance to our circulatory, nervous, endocrine and organ This restores the body and promotes our natural ability to heal With acupuncture, we can effectively prevent illness before it The acupuncture points chosen will depend on your condition, but you can expect five to Once the needles are inserted and you begin to feel relaxed, you will be able to lie comfortably with the needles in Your practitioner will come check on you during your session and this will be done quietly as to not disturb While resting with the needles, your body relaxes over the warmth of a BioMat, which empowers the circulatory system to increase and improve movement of blood, lymph and nutrients through the The needles used during acupuncture are different from any other type of medical They are fine and flexible and are usually inserted without any initial Once your energy is successfully conducted by the insertion of the needle, people report experiencing a sense of heaviness, numbness or electric stimulation at the needle site, or along the accompanying portion of the acupuncture channel being Because these sensations are new, they can cause mild discomfort at first, still patients often find the treatments to be quite How many treatments? The benefits of acupuncture are cumulative and occur exponentially, so more then one treatment is For acute, or conditions, you can expect to have four to treatments, but you will usually begin to feel relief after your first Chronic conditions may take longer to respond to treatment, depending on the type, severity and duration of the Preventative treatments and those for general may also be scheduled on an Our goal at Be Well Holistic Care is exactly the same as your We want you to feel better as soon as Your body will inform us of how often treatment is needed, and will set the pace for your Is Acupuncture Safe? Acupuncture is used by millions of Americans every Licensed acupuncturists must first earn a Bachelor of Science in Health Studies and Master of Science in Oriental During this time, they must undergo an extensive didactic and immersive clinical education program including the study of human anatomy and physiology, the biology and blood chemistry of a healthy human, and what changes take place when various pathologies appear and interrupt body Both pharmacological and intensive herbal medical study are required as well as the successful acquiring of a certification in Clean Needle Practitioners at

Bipolar II disorder (also known as bipolar two) affects about 2% of the Moods in bipolar II disorder cycle between highs and lows over time, similar to those in bipolar When bipolar II disorder is present, the ‚Äòup‚Äô moods never reach the mania Bipolar II disorder is characterized by less intense elevated moods called hypomanic Hypomania occurs at least once in the life of a bipolar II The majority of people with bipolar II disorder have episodes of depression more often than It is from this standpoint that ‚Äúmanic depression‚Äù was The majority of people with bipolar II disorder lead relatively normal lives between episodes of hypomania and Check: Anxiety Who is at risk for bipolar II disorder? The disorder can affect Bipolar disorder affects approximately % of the population ‚Äì nearly 6 million A person with bipolar disorder usually shows symptoms in their teens or early Most people who suffer from bipolar 2 disorder develop it before the age of Bipolar patients are at a higher risk if they have immediate family members with the What are the symptoms of bipolar II disorder? Hypomania is characterized by either high mood (feeling ‚Äúhigh‚Äù) or During hypomanic episodes, you may experience: Jumping from one idea to another suddenly Being overconfident Rapid, ‚Äúpressured‚Äù (uninterrupted) and loud speech An increase in energy decreased sleep needs and hyperactivity It is often pleasant to spend time with individuals who have hypomanic It is common for them to appear as the life of the party, making jokes, showing a keen interest in others and activities, and spreading a positive You might wonder, why is that such a bad thing?
